                         Content: V.c. 6.n.38.39.&c.-->] </inline> so that when a dry Summer followeth a moist Spring, the Bee-folds are rich. If the Summer be also moist, the increase of Bees will be greater: but, because of the scarcity of hony, this increase will proove a decrease: the more swarmes you have at the end of this Summer, the fewer stalls shall you have at the beginning of the next. For, except some faire rathe swarmes, and some good stockes, which cast betimes or not at all, they die all for hunger; when they have spent their own pittance, and spoiled their fellowes. How to prevent this poverty, see <!--An internal link should have been created here,
