                         Content: *--> continue longer, and doe more kindly worke their effects. So that wee may conclude with ‘<inline font-style="italic" font-weight="normal"><inline font-style="italic">Ecclesiasticus, cap.</inline> 11.3.</inline> <inline font-style="italic">The Bee is little among such as flye: but hir Fruit is the chiefe of sweet things.</inline>’</block><block text-indent="0pt" end-indent="12pt" start-indent="12pt" font-size="6pt" space-before.optimum="4pt" space-after.optimum="4pt">*‘<inline font-style="italic" font-weight="normal">Ex melle confectus syrupus diutius asservatur; is quoque magis incidit, ac detergit. Ex Saccharo suavior, sed non aeque efficax.</inline> <inline font-style="italic" font-weight="normal"><inline font-style="italic">Fern.Meth.l.</inline> 4.c.12.</inline>’</block><block line-height="1" text-indent="1em" space-before.optimum="0pt" space-before.maximum="12pt"><inline font-size="9pt" font-style="italic"> [Note: 18. <inline font-style="italic">Honie good in outward medicines.</inline>] </inline> Honie is used in outward medicines for divers purposes: <!--An internal link should have been created here,
                         but either there was no target, or no content to 
                         constitute the link.
